-- CTC Media’s Moscow Audience Rises in Week to May 20, TNS Says
-- B y   H a l i a   P a v l i v a
-- 2012-05-22T20:35:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-22/ctc-media-s-moscow-audience-rises-in-week-to-may-20-tns-says.html
CTC Media Inc. (CTCM) ’s average daily share
of viewers in Moscow aged 18-years-old and above rose to 5.8
percent in the week to May 20, outpacing REN TV and making it
the fifth-most watched television channel in Moscow, data
compiled by TNS-Global show.  The share of viewers in Moscow for the CTC TV channel, the
Nasdaq-listed Russian media company’s biggest source of revenue,
gained from 5.7 percent in the week to May 13, when it was
behind REN TV, data researcher TNS-Global said in an e-mail
today. NTV Television, Pervyi Kanal, Rossiya-1 and TNT ranked
ahead of CTC among Moscow viewers in the week to May 20, TNS-
Global data show.  The average daily audience among viewers four-years-old and
over in Moscow for CTC rose to 6.4 percent in the week to May 20
from 6.3 percent in the previous week, making it the fifth-most-
watched in audience rankings, the data show. Pervyi Kanal, NTV
Television, Rossiya-1 and TNT ranked ahead of CTC, TNS-Global
said. CTC outpaced REN TV, which came in fifth in the week to
May 13.  To contact the reporter on this story:
